    "alt": "Pasted image 20201026231409.png"
  })), "\nGiven the level of scalability and flexibility the microservice fad has brought to the tech world, are there other places currently served by traditional software designs and methodologies that could be supplanted by these techniques? I definitely think the capacity exists in most storage heavy paradigms, such as databases, personal data management, etc. It would be really interesting, even just as an exercise, to work up the whole 'personal datavault' project with a microservices architecture, rather than a monolith. Just thinking about the productivity gains from being able to refactor independently makes me a little giddy. "));
